                  "height": 1
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "u3An6",
                  "name": "article-body",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 24,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "ul9t0",
                      "name": "introPara",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "conflict-free replicated data types (crdts) have fundamentally changed how we think about distributed systems. in this post, we'll walk through how we built a real-time collaboration engine from scratch, the trade-offs we encountered, and why crdts were the right choice for our use case.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 14
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "oPLJQ",
                      "name": "h2-section",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "gap": 8,
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "7VTAg",
                          "name": "h2Comment",
                          "fill": "$accent-green",
                          "content": "//",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 14
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "JoK0T",
                          "name": "h2Text",
                          "fill": "$text-emphasis",
                          "content": "understanding the problem space",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 18,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Ue3hj",
                      "name": "bodyPara1",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "traditional approaches to real-time collaboration rely on operational transformation (ot), which requires a central server to resolve conflicts. this works well for simple document editing, but breaks down when you need offline support, peer-to-peer sync, or complex data structures beyond plain text.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 14
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "KC6KJ",
                      "name": "bodyPara2",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "crdts solve this by ensuring that concurrent operations can be merged automatically without conflicts. each replica maintains its own state and can independently apply operations — convergence is mathematically guaranteed.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 14
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "ieVIb",
                      "name": "code-block",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "$bg-elevated",
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 1,
                        "fill": "$border-primary"
                      },
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "gap": 4,
                      "padding": 20,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "KMr4x",
                          "name": "codeLine1",
                          "fill": "$accent-green",
                          "content": "$ interface CRDTDocument<T> {",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "rVUqw",
                          "name": "codeLine2",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "content": "    state: T;",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "ss53e",
                          "name": "codeLine3",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "content": "    merge(remote: T): T;",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "yzbTg",
                          "name": "codeLine4",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "content": "    apply(op: Operation): T;",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "dWh0b",
                          "name": "codeLine5",
                          "fill": "$accent-green",
                          "content": "}",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "AB2rV",
                      "name": "blockquote",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": {
                          "left": 2
                        },
                        "fill": "$accent-green"
                      },
                      "gap": 16,
                      "padding": [
                        16,
                        20
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "CvJ9b",
                          "name": "quoteText",
                          "fill": "$text-secondary",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "\"the key insight is that crdts trade space complexity for coordination freedom. you pay with memory, but you gain the ability to work independently without any central authority.\"",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                          "fontSize": 13,
                          "fontStyle": "italic"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "rXB6q",
                      "name": "h2-section-2",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "gap": 8,
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "v3YNz",
                          "name": "h2Comment2",
                          "fill": "$accent-green",
                          "content": "//",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 14
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "96CbS",
                          "name": "h2Text2",
                          "fill": "$text-emphasis",
                          "content": "implementation details",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 18,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Zgj55",
                      "name": "bodyPara3",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "we chose to implement a hybrid approach combining last-writer-wins registers for simple properties with sequence crdts for ordered collections. the architecture splits into three layers: the local state manager, the sync protocol handler, and the conflict resolution engine.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 14
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "tOHj2",
                      "name": "bodyPara4",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "the sync protocol uses a vector clock to track causality between operations. when two replicas reconnect after being offline, they exchange only the operations that the other hasn't seen yet — making sync bandwidth-efficient even after long periods of disconnection.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 14
                    }
                  ]
                },
